    "body": "Hi @b-m-f , \r\nExactly! Sorry I didn't give extra detail in the issue, I should have been more verbose, but you've tracked it down it seems!\r\n\r\nI've just had a quick look at this, and my first thought too was to save on shutdown. However, it's quite important for discovery that we don't lose our updated ENR's, which we might do for ungraceful shutdowns. \r\n\r\nAlso, I realize that I don't expose the updated ENR, so we don't actually have anything to save :p. \r\n\r\nI think perhaps, the best way, would be to save it, when it gets updated: \r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/eth2-libp2p/src/discovery.rs#L204\r\n\r\nThis can be done by accessing the updated ENR from the discovery, like\r\n```rust\r\nlet enr = self.discovery.local_enr()\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhich comes from here: https://github.com/sigp/rust-libp2p/blob/lighthouse/misc/discv5/src/behaviour.rs#L169\r\n\r\nGiven that you have the ENR, you should be able to save it.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
